<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="12" pageNumber="89" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="12" pageNumber="89">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="90" pageId="12" pageNumber="89">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Macrocheilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrocheilus cheni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="89" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheni">Macrocheilus cheni</taxonomicName>
but easily distinguishable from the latter by the presence of additional setae between the anterior and anterior setae, the median tooth of the mentum with sinuate lateral margins in middle (sinuate on api 
<pageBreakToken pageId="13" pageNumber="90" start="start">cal</pageBreakToken>
one-third in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Macrocheilus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Macrocheilus cheni" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheni">Macrocheilus cheni</taxonomicName>
), the median lobe larger, and the apical lamella long and narrowed towards apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
